# Trowser

This full-screen modal is the right fit when customers need to create, view, or edit a transaction.
Use a trowser when the user needs to fill out a complex form.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/trowser
```

```tsx
import { Trowser } from '@ids-ts/trowser';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `disableAutoFocus` | `boolean` | No | * disableAutoFocus: If true, would not put focus on first tabbable element. |
| `disableRestoreFocus` | `boolean` | No | if true, does not focus back on the element that initiated |
| `refocus` | `boolean` | No | when true, will refocus the trowser |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | used for functional tests. |
| `children` | `React.ReactElement | React.ReactElement[]` | Yes | inner content of trowser, e.g. form elements or menu items |
| `className` | `string` | No | class name for the trowser |
| `disableTrowserHeaderOnMobileStepflow` | `boolean` | No | disable the trowser header in its entirety when the trowser is rendered on a tablet or phone and stepFlow={true} is set |
| `dismissible` | `boolean` | No | shows X button, on screen size < 768px the dismissible prop will always be true |
| `feedback` | `boolean` | No | shows give feedback button |
| `feedbackLabel` | `string` | No | label to change feedback label text |
| `footerButton` | `React.ReactElement[]` | No | array of different type of buttons that can be rendered |
| `panelContent` | `React.ReactElement` | No | render panel component either on the left or right |
| `footerCenterLinkActions` | `((event: React.MouseEvent<HTMLButtonElement>) => void)[]` | No | Array of callback functions for center footer links. |
| `footerCenterLinkLabels` | `string[]` | No | an array of labels for center footer links |
| `moreButton` | `React.ReactElement` | No | - |
| `hideOverflow` | `boolean` | No | - |
| `help` | `boolean` | No | shows help button |
| `helpLabel` | `string` | No | label to change help label in overflow menu and aria text |
| `history` | `boolean` | No | shows history button |
| `historyLabel` | `string` | No | label to change history label in overflow menu and aria text |
| `headerClassName` | `string` | No | Custom className for header |
| `headerRightContent` | `React.ReactNode` | No | Custom React content to render in the header right section before icons |
| `isFeedbackMenuOpen` | `boolean` | No | boolean flag to indicate whether feedback menu is open or not |
| `isHistoryMenuOpen` | `boolean` | No | boolean flag to indicate whether history menu is open or not |
| `isHelpMenuOpen` | `boolean` | No | boolean flag to indicate whether help menu is open or not |
| `isSearchMenuOpen` | `boolean` | No | boolean flag to indicate whether search menu is open or not |
| `isSettingsMenuOpen` | `boolean` | No | boolean flag to indicate whether settings menu is open or not |
| `light` | `boolean` | No | Whether the light mode theme is being used or not |
| `onClose` | `() => void` | No | callback for when trowser is closed |
| `onFeedbackIconClick` | `MouseOrKeyboardEventFunction` | No | callback for when feedback icon clicked |
| `onHelpIconClick` | `MouseOrKeyboardEventFunction` | No | callback for when icon clicked |
| `onHistoryIconClick` | `MouseOrKeyboardEventFunction` | No | callback for when icon clicked |
| `onKeyDown` | `KeyboardDIVEventFunction` | No | callback for when a key is pressed |
| `onSearchIconClick` | `MouseOrKeyboardEventFunction` | No | callback for when search icon clicked |
| `onSettingsIconClick` | `MouseOrKeyboardEventFunction` | No | callback for when icon clicked |
| `onShow` | `EnterHandler<undefined>` | No | callback for when trowser is shown |
| `sectionClassName` | `string` | No | class name for body content of trowser |
| `search` | `boolean` | No | shows search button |
| `searchLabel` | `string` | No | label to change search label in overflow menu and aria text |
| `settings` | `boolean` | No | shows settings button |
| `settingsLabel` | `string` | No | label to change settings label in overflow menu and aria text |
| `showCancelFooterButton` | `boolean` | No | whether to show the cancel link in the footer |
| `open` | `boolean` | No | whether to show the popover |
| `overflowIconLabel` | `string` | No | aria label for the overflow icon on mobile |
| `overflowDoneLabel` | `string` | No | label for the done button in the mobile overflow menu |
| `renderFlyout` | `RenderFlyoutType` | No | Render menu function |
| `title` | `string` | No | trowser title |
| `stepFlow` | `boolean` | No | Use as stepFlow={true} when the section contains a Step Flow component, removes footer. |
| `stageContent` | `string | React.ReactElement` | No | The inner content of stage area |
| `stageClassName` | `string` | No | CSS ClassName for allowing custom CSS for staging |
| `trowserZIndex` | `number` | No | - |
| `cancelFooterButtonLabel` | `string` | No | Prop to set the label for Cancel button as per user's choice |
| `theme` | `string` | No | Product Theme type to render the footer |
| `backgroundColor` | `BackgroundColorType` | No | background color for body content of trowser |

